WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.820 --> 00:00:05.380
Welcome to the latest series from AJ+.

00:00:07.300 --> 00:00:10.480
"San Francisco's Chinatown is the oldest Chinatown in America."

00:00:10.480 --> 00:00:13.360
"There's not too many places left in the world like this."

00:00:14.080 --> 00:00:18.480
We're all about telling the stories of the underrepresented and misunderstood communities

00:00:18.480 --> 00:00:19.680
that make up our country.

00:00:19.840 --> 00:00:22.240
"What does it mean to be both Iranian and American?"

00:00:22.680 --> 00:00:26.420
"When telling the story of Syrians in America, I'm in a way telling my own story."

00:00:26.720 --> 00:00:28.980
By speaking with people on the ground.

00:00:28.980 --> 00:00:33.020
"When people think of Chicago, they think 'Oh my God, it's a violent place with crazy people.'

00:00:33.020 --> 00:00:34.260
And that's not the truth."

00:00:34.260 --> 00:00:35.340
"We don't look like American

00:00:36.500 --> 00:00:37.660
people?"

00:00:38.740 --> 00:00:43.680
Join us as we visit a new community each month to learn more about their place in U.S. history,

00:00:43.680 --> 00:00:47.920
what they're facing today, and how they're preserving their culture for future generations.

00:00:52.640 --> 00:00:55.560
Follow us for more Untold America.

